        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Gunkk</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> For quests, hail Noclin to get his pet's femur.  Nice 1hb for a newb necro.  I didn't bother with anything else.  The next quests start around level 30 I think... cave bad lord -&gt; so-and-so's Hat.</P><P>For exp beyond the newbie zone, go to Toxx and hunt whatever is white/blue until you can take the Kobold camps (level 7-8?).  </P><P>9-10 lowbie Kobolds in Warrens or skelly miners/Abandoned Heretic Pet at Toxx/Paineel zone line.</P><P>10-17  Kurns Tower in Field of Bone -- good exp, lots of bone chips, and practice with evocation &lt;-- important later on!  I know it's far, but it's worth the trip!  Bring your 16 spells with you if you can afford the coin and inventory space.</P><P>17-24 Shrooms and Patogs in Paludal Caverns past bandit camp near Shadow Haven.</P><P>25-31 Needlite Cave in Echo Caverns.</P><P>31-34 Named Sisters and/or Dwarfs on Sisters Isle in OOT.  WC tollbooth guards.  Soloing giants/burynai/gobbies near BW zone in Frontier Mountains.  Lots of options here.  </P><P>35-37 Drakkel wolves in Great Divide, Terrors in Crystal Caverns (or partner with Geos, group on spiders).  WC tollbooth guards.  Lots of options here too.  </P><P>37-39 Anything dark blue in the Overthere.  Bank, vendors, and guards in the zone are friendly to Erudites.</P><P><BR>[changed Gnolls to Kobolds]</P><P>Edited by - Gunkk on 07/26/2002  08:35:30</font></td>
