        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Nefarietteeci</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Being an Erudite Necro has been great fun so far!</P><P>1. Use the newbie zone for all it's worth. It's, IMO, easily the best newbie zone in the game. Always remember it when you need bone chips. I used to come back every spell level to pick up my spells, train and load up on bone chips.</P><P>2. Head out into Tox. It was my goal not to leave the continent (this was before the Warrens) until I had Gather Shadows. Getting to level 5 is easy enough in the newbie area. Then when you're ready (6?) you can camp the Abandon Heretic Pet that wanders from just outside the enterance to Paineel. He's maybe on a 8 minute timer and works well. No faction hit. </P><P>3. Next you can camp the two skel miners in the tunnel to Paineel. Park your pet outside 'cause the pathing is bad and he'll wander off into Toxx if you try to get him to follow you. Alternatively, you can summon your pet in the tunnel, then you're fine (once the spawn is broken). No faction hit and they'll be indiff to you, though you can pull both as I recall, so be careful when breaking the spawn.</P><P>4. At 8 you can head out into the wide world. I believe I went and did sirens in OOT. I have a thing for hunting on islands. I used them First the one spawn, then the two spawn, then all 3 to get to 14 or so, then I think I drained the ones closer to the BB zone for another level to 15. Sirens used to be popular, I don't know if they still are.</P><P>5. Then off to Timorous Deep for some more Island hunting. Take on the Fallen Iksar on (what else!) Fallen Iksar Island. Great fun, bone chips, rarely camped. I think I used them to about level 18</P><P>6. Then back home for a reunion of sorts with your arch enemies, the Eruidtes! I hunted Phalean Highbrow (??) in the Bluehawk Inn for a couple levels. No problem if you're not KoS, which you shouldn't be. I think that can take you to 20 or 21</P><P>Then I think I hunted the Bard in Erudin. After that things got a little messy, and I don't recall exactly what I did. </P><P>From 29-36 or so I hunted Ortallius in SRo. Killed my faction with the Temple of Sol Ro, which I'm kinda regretting now, but it's (hopefully) recoverable by slaughtering shadowmen or paying lots of plat to the merchant behind Ort (already paid him 600 pp and they're still KoS).</P><P>Anyway, those are some ideas to last you for a bit. The hardest part starting out was getting from where the newbie zone isn't much good to the point where I could handle the abandon heretic pet, as I recall.</P><P>Still a good time all around. I regret some of my faction killing, but in the end it was probably worth it. I'm also a slow XPer, there are probably lots of spaces that will rocket you through the levels quicker if you're a bit more ambitious.</P><P>Nefariette<BR>51 Heretic<BR>E'ci</P><P> </font></td>
