        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Raejin</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Do all of the Abbatoir Initiate Quests, free armor and it all has +Int on it. The quest for the staff is kinda bogus, really hard and its only 2 int and 2hb. Look it up on AllaKhazam's site, its really easy and its all on Odus.</P><P>Doing Misty Storyswapper from 12-16 got me just over 100pp after buying spells (what I felt was necessary including L.SummonCorpse) and I got the levels in a few hours.</P><P>The thing with doing Misty at 12 is this.. don't fear kite her! Fear and darkness will almost always be resisted. Instead, do heat blood (she only resisted this once out of the 100+ kills), send pet, TAKE THE HITS until you're at 40 or 60% health, step back and toss lifedraws at her (should take 2 or 3) until she's dead. Yes, her HP is that low. I also killed Guard Gregor who was white at 12 (fear kite) drops Qeynos Citizens. I killed the caster and the pally nearby as well, also white to 12. Fear kite. Pally gives all around bad qeynos faction, guards, pallies, clerics. Gives good Bloodsabre faction! The caster can be tough, sometimes tougher than misty even though he is several levels lower. His nukes can do over 30 and he can root your pet. Fear kite him, drop everything on him, he'll die. Drops the generic qeynos faction and the Qeynos caster guild faction. Although the 2 NPCs are close together but will not assist each other. Starting out as an erudite necromancer, I started dubious to bards, indifferent to bloodsabres, dubious to pallies, and kos to casters. Left kos to all except bloodsabres which went to amiable. The pally and wizard drop heads and I'm not sure what they're for yet. They're not listed on AllaKhazam's bestiary so I'm guessing they're new. Gregor drops a note and I can't read it (its in thieve's cant). What's odd about him is that he's a guard and doesn't drop any qeynos guard faction, and his helmet is on sideways.. I'm guessing he's a spy of somesort. Haven't looked him up yet.</P><P>I'm level 16 now, and kind of frustrated because I found a nice guy to kill. His name is Lars McMannus, he's on a 6 minute timer near the shore of the barbarian fishing village in WK. He is BARELY fear kite-able, but it can be done (sometimes with losing a pet). He sometimes drops research, and FS daggers/spears/rapiers. The problem is that there's a level 30+ called Ulrich McMannus that "patrols" the fishing village. Thanks to a bug sometimes Ulrich McMannus will "warp" (I've seen it happen) even if he's way up on top of the hill and you have Lars way down the shore. He will beat the crap out of your pet. If this happens finish Lars up with lifedraws, FD and /q out to remove aggro (Ulrich is 30+ and has a chance to still remember you, so its best to /q to completly remove your aggro). I'll probably leave this spot because of this bug, but its hard to leave the 4% exp per kill of Lars and FS weapons.</P><P>I tried the bard at the spires in NK, something Minster. This camp has a few problems, if she's alive too long while you fear kite her, she'll get killed by the wildlife (seen a griffawn kill her before I learned I had to stop pulling her out that far) which will poof her corpse and you won't get exp. Also, Guard Fredrick will sometimes roam through the spires and you will be KOS. Third, sometimes people waiting for a port to Luclin at the spires will kill her. Fourth, You have to get out of the spires while it ports or you'll get ported to the gypsie camp (if you don't have a shard, if you do have one you'll get ported to Luclin). Finally, she isn't as much exp as Lars and her loot isn't as good as Lars or Misty. It is easy to get a sow from all the people at the spires though.</P><P>And yeah, I like killing NPCs more than random un-named wildlife. Might go try Jonah although he seems kinda low to kill at 16.</P><P><b>Yiteryen, 16th Erudite Necromancer</b><BR>Tunare</P><P> </font></td>
